Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[Eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode \N988 "The Feuding Girls"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[OP]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,[ED]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.48,0:00:03.99,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,Are we really doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.99,0:00:06.80,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. After all, she's bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.80,0:00:08.68,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,If we're doing this, now's our chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.68,0:00:12.64,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,But if someone finds out, \Nwe'll both be arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.64,0:00:17.75,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,Nah. Our alibis are perfect, and \NI'll be the one to finish her off.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.75,0:00:19.99,DCMain,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,Got it. Let's do it, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.88,0:00:26.96,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's shop!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.96,0:00:29.81,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,We're here for products available today only.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.81,0:00:31.45,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Clothes and accessories.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.45,0:00:33.63,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get pumped!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.63,0:00:34.72,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.69,0:00:36.82,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.82,0:00:38.85,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Happy Seal, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.18,0:00:42.60,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Go, go! Go, go! Go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.78,0:00:45.23,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Happy Seal, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.52,0:00:48.94,Mina,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Komoro Mina (23) \NBlue Model
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.72,0:00:48.19,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}This is the current top lovely toy!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.19,0:00:50.48,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The number one soothing-type toy!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.81,0:00:53.22,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Such a wonderful partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.32,0:00:54.74,Ayaka,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Saijo Ayaka (22) \NRed Model
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.22,0:00:55.41,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He'll always be with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.07,0:00:59.12,Mai,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Fukamoto Mai (22) \NYellow Model
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.26,0:01:00.58,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He laughs, he cries, he sleeps, he \Nwakes up, and he dances beautifully!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.74,0:01:04.16,Yuko,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Oyodo Yuko (21) \NPink Model
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.96,0:01:04.09,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You can control him using the smartphone app!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.83,0:01:08.58,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Happy Seal, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.58,0:01:11.59,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Go, go! Go, go! Go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.01,0:01:11.59,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, so it's a seal toy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.73,0:01:18.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.84,0:01:23.35,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry suddenly asking \Nyou to take some time off for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.35,0:01:28.52,Yasuda,NAMETAG,0000,0000,0000,,Yasuda
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.52,0:01:26.94,Kazuo,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Yasuda Kazuo (43) \NManager
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.68,0:01:27.93,DCMain,YASUDA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's fine. We're much obliged to your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.93,0:01:28.52,DCMain,YASUDA,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.74,0:01:30.45,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.45,0:01:35.40,DCMain,YASUDA,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko-san, if you'd only asked, we would \Nhave set aside some limited products for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.71,0:01:37.39,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's not good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.39,0:01:40.66,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I have to get it myself in order to—
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.14,0:01:42.41,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Ayaka-chan, hurry up and move some stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.41,0:01:46.79,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What? But I just painted my nails.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.65,0:01:48.67,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.47,0:01:52.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's those girls from earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.00,0:01:57.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Find the question that solves the mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.66,0:01:59.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apply miraculous detective skills \Nto the secrets of the heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.94,0:02:01.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A secret battle between a group of girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.80,0:02:03.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A case breaks out backstage!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.79,0:02:05.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.46,0:02:07.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.24,0:02:10.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.00,0:03:56.00,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(396,1)}The Feuding Girls
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.69,0:03:52.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Feuding Girls!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.53,0:04:00.51,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,You knew from the start that \Nwe'd be carrying stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.77,0:04:04.63,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I won an \Naudition for a commercial.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.63,0:04:06.41,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I need to look pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.32,0:04:09.12,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Mai, you were rejected, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.12,0:04:10.43,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,That's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.05,0:04:12.02,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,Ayaka-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.28,0:04:15.52,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, please. You're both scowling.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.07,0:04:18.94,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,Mai?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.37,0:04:27.47,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave this stuff here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.47,0:04:29.87,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ayaka-san, help carry something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.25,0:04:34.32,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Mina-san, can I take tomorrow off?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.32,0:04:36.69,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to practice for my commercial.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.69,0:04:40.91,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on. You can't suddenly \Nask for the day off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.91,0:04:42.34,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Yuko-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.55,0:04:43.60,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.60,0:04:45.65,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, if you work hard on this job,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.65,0:04:48.56,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,you might get an even better offer next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.56,0:04:49.75,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.75,0:04:55.23,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But wouldn't trying hard on the commercial \Nget me an even better job than this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.43,0:04:58.66,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,Ayaka, are you making fun of this job?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.66,0:04:59.61,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Mina-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.77,0:05:02.28,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.28,0:05:03.95,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.90,0:05:09.27,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ayaka-san, you're acting \Na little strange today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.27,0:05:10.50,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Try to be more considerate of the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.50,0:05:12.18,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,Just ignore her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.18,0:05:16.05,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't want to do this \Ntough low-paying job anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.05,0:05:16.79,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.83,0:05:22.53,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.53,0:05:24.21,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, you're clumsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.21,0:05:27.14,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,Ayaka! You did that on purpose, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.14,0:05:29.14,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What? On purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.14,0:05:29.97,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,How could you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.97,0:05:31.43,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.60,0:05:33.68,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Ow! What was that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.16,0:05:37.19,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop, both of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.42,0:05:42.02,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try to get along while we're \Nworking on this campaign, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.02,0:05:44.94,DCMain,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,God, you're so annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.86,0:05:51.33,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.76,0:05:53.54,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Did we get any on you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.54,0:05:55.66,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.66,0:05:57.66,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.46,0:06:20.40,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The limited products go on sale soon, Sonoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.40,0:06:24.18,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It was worth standing \Nin line for thirty minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.54,0:06:28.36,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you spacing out for?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.36,0:06:29.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.17,0:06:34.79,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.98,0:06:40.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.99,0:06:42.63,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,A-Ayaka is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.62,0:06:52.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.70,0:06:54.89,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,No way. Ayaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.91,0:06:57.21,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did she fall from there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.21,0:06:58.93,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.93,0:07:00.13,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.13,0:07:02.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Call the police, Ran-neechan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.09,0:07:03.77,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.46,0:07:08.57,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.33,0:07:16.49,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The estimated time of death is around 2:30PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.49,0:07:19.36,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,This storage room within a shopping \Nmall where the crime took place
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.36,0:07:20.91,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,happens to be under construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.19,0:07:26.67,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The victim Saijo Ayaka-san seems to have \Nfallen from the construction scaffolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.84,0:07:28.18,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.18,0:07:30.14,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Which means this was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.14,0:07:32.05,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.45,0:07:36.31,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There were signs that the scaffolding the \Nvictim fell from had been tampered with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.31,0:07:41.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What? Which means this could be a murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.50,0:07:42.44,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.22,0:07:48.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And? Who are these three?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.54,0:07:51.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,They're colleagues of the late Ayaka-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.27,0:07:54.11,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Fukamoto Mai-san discovered the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.11,0:07:57.68,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Could you describe the circumstances \Nunder which you found her?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.68,0:08:01.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, everyone \Nwas arguing with Ayaka-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.71,0:08:03.29,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.42,0:08:05.40,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true, Ran-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.40,0:08:07.38,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.78,0:08:08.96,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.18,0:08:10.64,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.64,0:08:13.41,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that we argued with Ayaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.41,0:08:15.26,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.26,0:08:16.96,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,We wouldn't kill Ayaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.96,0:08:18.22,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.47,0:08:23.23,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Then where were you around \N2:30PM when Ayaka-san died?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.56,0:08:25.26,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.26,0:08:26.66,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.66,0:08:31.74,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I was here preparing for the sale \Nthis afternoon along with the staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.49,0:08:35.24,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And? What about you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.85,0:08:42.55,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,I was actually skipping work to watch \Nthe concert going on in the event space.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.55,0:08:43.81,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,Mina-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.81,0:08:44.87,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.26,0:08:46.73,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.73,0:08:48.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.21,0:08:56.80,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, we found this in the \Ngarbage can in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.22,0:09:01.12,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,"Dear Mai, sorry about \Nearlier. I got carried away."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.12,0:09:05.31,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,"I'd like to apologize, so please come to \Nfloor 2, section 3 of the storage room around 3PM."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.66,0:09:06.88,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,"From Ayaka."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.09,0:09:09.82,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.57,0:09:16.32,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Also, we also found this at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.45,0:09:19.08,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's Mai-san's...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.85,0:09:22.64,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you certain this is yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.64,0:09:25.23,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, b-but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.23,0:09:26.83,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Is this what happened, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.26,0:09:32.05,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Mai-san received a letter from Ayaka-san \Nsaying she wanted to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.05,0:09:36.10,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,She secretly went to the storage \Nroom and broke the scaffolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.10,0:09:40.85,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Then she feigned innocence and met Ayaka-san \Non the second floor of the storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.33,0:09:46.73,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But she dropped her brooch then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.73,0:09:47.52,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.99,0:09:49.77,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.23,0:09:52.36,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that I went to the storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.36,0:09:54.28,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,Ayaka said she wanted to apologize...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.59,0:09:56.67,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.67,0:10:00.02,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,By the time I went, Ayaka was already dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.02,0:10:01.78,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,You have to believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.47,0:10:27.56,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do that, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.80,0:10:29.65,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't wander around the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.65,0:10:30.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.94,0:10:33.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-neechan, doesn't this \Nseem the other way around?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.34,0:10:35.23,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The other way around?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.51,0:10:39.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It was Ayaka-san who \Nasked Mai-san to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.64,0:10:43.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But Mai-san is thought to have \Ntampered with the scaffolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.18,0:10:50.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Normally wouldn't the person who did \Nthe tampering invite their victim here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.01,0:10:52.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.48,0:10:55.38,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But that would mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.25,0:11:00.43,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That marks where Mai-san's \Nbrooch fell, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.43,0:11:02.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.69,0:11:04.17,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if it's the other way around, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.17,0:11:04.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.78,0:11:14.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Ran-neechan?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.76,0:11:17.33,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Thanks, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.08,0:11:21.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.12,0:11:23.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The belt holding it in place is loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.52,0:11:27.50,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.63,0:11:34.43,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's Ayaka-san's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.63,0:11:37.11,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.11,0:11:37.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.91,0:11:39.30,DCMain,TASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.37,0:11:43.01,DCMain,TASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,You can't come in here! It's off limits!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.01,0:11:44.90,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.90,0:11:45.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.39,0:11:49.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The belt around these boxes is \Nloose. They're about to fall over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.98,0:11:51.02,DCMain,TASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,It's what?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.61,0:11:54.13,DCMain,TASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. Must've been those part-timers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.13,0:11:55.77,DCMain,TASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have to give them a talking to later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.04,0:11:58.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Those? There's more than one of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.15,0:12:00.36,DCMain,TASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.36,0:12:03.32,DCMain,TASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,One of them lifts boxes using that crane,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.88,0:12:06.70,DCMain,TASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,and the other stacks and \Nsecures them in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.02,0:12:09.70,DCMain,TASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,It takes at least two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.57,0:12:11.92,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Two people?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.46,0:12:16.30,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, that brooch has been \Nmissing since a few days ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.30,0:12:17.46,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,I've been looking for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.74,0:12:21.59,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But you tried to hide the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.59,0:12:24.63,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,Because I didn't want to become a suspect!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.89,0:12:30.45,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you were the runner-up \Nat an audition for a commercial.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.45,0:12:32.64,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,If something happened to Ayaka-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.78,0:12:35.40,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,N-No. I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.82,0:12:41.65,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? You want to confirm my alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.90,0:12:45.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Do you know who Mori Kogoro is?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.23,0:12:46.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.37,0:12:48.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He wants to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.39,0:12:58.04,DCMain,YAMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuko-chan was in the green \Nroom with me when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.44,0:13:00.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So you didn't go to that storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.18,0:13:04.42,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. I haven't been there \Nonce this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.41,0:13:07.93,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Mori is asking about my alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.14,0:13:11.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. You said you went to watch the concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.98,0:13:14.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He was wondering if there was \Nanyone who could vouch for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.24,0:13:18.68,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,I know the receptionist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.68,0:13:20.35,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,You should ask her about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.76,0:13:34.06,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They both have alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.74,0:13:36.85,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's not related after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.79,0:13:38.65,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.14,0:13:41.98,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, there you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.98,0:13:43.46,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.46,0:13:44.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.45,0:13:47.23,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,No. I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.23,0:13:50.23,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't push Ayaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.41,0:13:52.34,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Now, now. You can tell us \Nthe rest at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.36,0:14:04.59,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.31,0:14:11.69,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,Please believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.69,0:14:13.29,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,I really didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.52,0:14:16.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, you can tell us the rest at—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.33,0:14:18.29,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.64,0:14:27.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Sonoko-neechan?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.36,0:14:30.69,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.69,0:14:34.18,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just feeling a little dizzy \Nbecause I figured it all out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.18,0:14:35.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.11,0:14:36.93,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You know who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.21,0:14:38.48,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.48,0:14:39.69,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,In order to confirm my suspicions,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.69,0:14:43.94,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,could you go up to the second floor \Nwhere Ayaka-san fell, Detective Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.03,0:14:49.20,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What are you having Takagi-kun confirm?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.59,0:14:53.28,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,There were two tricks set \Nup inside this storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.28,0:14:54.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Two tricks?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.21,0:15:00.96,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The first was applied to the \Nscaffolding that made Ayaka-san fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.10,0:15:03.52,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,And the second was...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.52,0:15:04.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.66,0:15:06.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I've arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.14,0:15:08.72,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,See the boxes stacked there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.72,0:15:11.07,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't they seem unsteady,\Nlike they're about to fall over?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.38,0:15:15.32,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. It's dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.32,0:15:18.60,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,And where was Mai-san's brooch?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.84,0:15:20.35,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,In front of the boxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.83,0:15:23.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What about that, Sonoko-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.63,0:15:28.61,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi, could you look at the \Nclasp on the belt securing those boxes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.50,0:15:32.76,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There's some kind of \Npaint or something on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.76,0:15:35.08,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything on the floor nearby?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.50,0:15:39.29,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I found something!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.96,0:15:41.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.91,0:15:45.29,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Is it an artificial nail?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.54,0:15:47.31,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,That's Ayaka's.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.61,0:15:52.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The body was missing one of its nails.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.86,0:15:53.84,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.84,0:15:58.68,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,based on what we just confirmed and \NMai-san's testimony relating to her brooch...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.90,0:16:02.37,DCItalic,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, that brooch has been \Nmissing since a few days ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.37,0:16:03.69,DCItalic,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,I've been looking for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.97,0:16:08.53,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,And in conjunction with the letter \NAyaka-san wrote to Mai-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.53,0:16:09.11,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.80,0:16:13.45,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Ayaka-san stole Mai-san's \Nbrooch and left it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.85,0:16:15.81,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,She summoned Mai-san here with that letter
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.81,0:16:20.83,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and planned to send her and the scaffolding \Ncrashing to the floor by knocking over the boxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.80,0:16:22.96,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.31,0:16:24.94,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,Ayaka was going to kill me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.43,0:16:29.80,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But something made her lose her footing \Non the scaffolding she tampered with
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.80,0:16:31.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and she fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.37,0:16:32.31,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.31,0:16:33.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.37,0:16:34.97,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.14,0:16:39.22,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Boxes can't be stacked on the \Nsecond floor without two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.76,0:16:44.48,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,One lifts the boxes using the crane, \Nwhile the other stacks them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.96,0:16:48.36,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, someone \Nwas controlling the crane.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.88,0:16:54.49,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,An evil seal who incited Ayaka-san and \Ngot her caught up in this murder plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.76,0:16:57.14,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,They incited Ayaka-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.14,0:16:58.74,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. For example...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.52,0:17:03.83,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,"She's planning to injure you \Nand steal your commercial job."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.83,0:17:06.50,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,"She did the same thing to me \Nbefore and took one of mine."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.76,0:17:10.70,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,"At this rate, she'll continue to \Nescalate, and harm the two of us."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.18,0:17:13.51,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,"We should kill Mai-san together."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.30,0:17:19.01,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Then the evil seal instructed \NAyaka-san to do the following.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.66,0:17:22.27,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,"Write a letter to Mai-san inviting \Nher to the storage room."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.27,0:17:26.52,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,"Leave this brooch I stole from \Nher in front of the boxes."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.96,0:17:31.86,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,"Once Mai-san comes to the second floor, \Nshe'll spot her brooch and approach."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.86,0:17:35.76,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,"Then I'll push the boxes onto her \Nfrom behind, and she'll fall."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.76,0:17:37.59,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,"It'll look like an accident."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.59,0:17:40.96,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,"During that time,\Nyou'll go fabricate an alibi."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.54,0:17:47.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. But it was Ayaka-san, \Nnot Mai-san, who ended up dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.76,0:17:50.39,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Something must've made her fall from \Nthe scaffolding she tampered with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.39,0:17:52.94,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong, Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.30,0:17:56.75,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It was the evil seal who \Ntampered with the scaffolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.75,0:18:01.38,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ayaka-san climbed the scaffolding \Nwithout realizing that and fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.38,0:18:02.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.46,0:18:08.44,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The true goal of this murder \Nplot was to kill Ayaka-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.68,0:18:15.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But if killing Ayaka-san was their only goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.37,0:18:17.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,why bother with this troublesome trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.90,0:18:22.15,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,This trick was bait meant \Nto draw in Ayaka-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.15,0:18:23.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Bait?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.35,0:18:26.46,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,If they had invited Ayaka-san here \Nwith the intention of murdering her,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.46,0:18:29.35,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,it could have left behind evidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.86,0:18:33.80,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,or Ayaka-san herself could \Nhave told someone about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.02,0:18:39.11,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But by luring Ayaka-san into \Na fake plot to murder Mai-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.11,0:18:42.04,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,they didn't have to worry \Nabout her telling anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.04,0:18:45.83,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, the odds that suspicion \Nwould fall on the evil seal
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.83,0:18:47.81,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,would be reduced to nearly nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.05,0:18:49.18,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.18,0:18:53.72,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The letter to Mai-san was \Nproof of their quarrel,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.72,0:18:58.64,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and as the first person to discover the \Nbody, suspicion would fall on Mai-san first.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.68,0:19:05.08,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And the brooch at the crime scene would seem \Nlike evidence that Mai-san was the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.10,0:19:10.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But, Sonoko-kun, how did this \Nevil seal get Ayaka-san
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.98,0:19:15.30,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,to climb the scaffolding \Nthat had been tampered with?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.30,0:19:16.84,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Well... Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.02,0:19:18.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.47,0:19:23.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, there are lots of stuffed seals.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.92,0:19:25.75,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Stuffed seals?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.75,0:19:27.72,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.08,0:19:32.12,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Those stuffed animals can apparently \Nbe controlled using a smartphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.12,0:19:33.10,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.46,0:19:37.73,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,They told Ayaka-san exactly \Nwhen to place the brooch there,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.73,0:19:39.26,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.77,0:19:51.12,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.58,0:19:53.84,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,In order to control those stuffed animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.84,0:19:57.19,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,you need to register it on your phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.19,0:19:58.21,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.21,0:20:01.04,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,The stuffed animals over \Nthere haven't been sold yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.04,0:20:02.63,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,so they can't be controlled using a phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.63,0:20:04.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.65,0:20:07.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This seal has a stain on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.74,0:20:09.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a coffee stain?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.87,0:20:15.98,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, do you remember what happened \Nwhen we were in the green room?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.17,0:20:20.19,DCItalic,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,God, you're so annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.13,0:20:24.58,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yuko...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.58,0:20:26.07,DCMain,MINA,0000,0000,0000,,Did you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.50,0:20:31.58,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yuko-san, you said you hadn't \Nbeen here once all afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.09,0:20:35.50,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,So why is that stuffed animal here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.10,0:20:42.14,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,And if we examine your phone, we'll \Nfind that stuffed animal registered to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.14,0:20:50.22,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,She stole the man I loved \Nand tossed him aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.56,0:20:53.98,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,He killed himself because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.65,0:20:58.11,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,So I avenged him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.92,0:21:01.48,DCMain,MAI,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why frame me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.05,0:21:03.86,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Mai-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.86,0:21:05.99,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,It could've been anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.33,0:21:10.35,DCMain,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who might've argued with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.95,0:21:13.09,DCItalic,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Are we really doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.09,0:21:16.00,DCItalic,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. After all, she's bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.00,0:21:17.86,DCItalic,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,If we're doing this, now's our chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.86,0:21:21.84,DCItalic,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But if someone finds out, \Nwe'll both be arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.84,0:21:26.78,DCItalic,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Nah. Our alibis are perfect, and \NI'll be the one to finish her off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.33,0:21:30.51,DCItalic,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Got it. Let's kill Mai, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.07,0:21:35.52,DCItalic,YUKO,0000,0000,0000,,First, you'll trip me in front of everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.86,0:21:38.45,DCItalic,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,After making Mai angry,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.45,0:21:40.85,DCItalic,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send her a letter \Nsaying I want to apologize
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.85,0:21:42.96,DCItalic,AYAKA,0000,0000,0000,,and have her come to the storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.40,0:23:10.43,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.43,0:23:11.99,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.20,0:23:13.38,DCMain,YASUDA,0000,0000,0000,,They're flying off the shelves.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.38,0:23:14.49,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.49,0:23:17.75,DCMain,YASUDA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for even putting \Non the idol outfit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.03,0:23:20.50,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.50,0:23:22.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive as always, Ran-neechan.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.25,0:23:26.25,DCMain,YASUDA,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko-san, thank you for helping, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.09,0:23:30.47,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.47,0:23:32.26,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,This costume sure is hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.57,0:23:35.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed, Detective Queen Sonoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.08,0:23:36.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You look good in anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.85,0:23:38.81,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're next, kid. Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.81,0:23:40.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wait, wait!
